snippet.textDisplay: This is a type of coronavirus and it is not yet able to be diagnosed or treated. Thermal screening for fever is pointless, the fever does not start for 5 - 7 days. The virus can live for 5 days on surfaces and can be transmitted up to 7 ft. It can be the case that someone does have the virus and is not showing symptoms, but they are contagious. It takes around 5 - 7 day to become symptomatic and this is like a severe cold or even influenza. Those who are vulnerable are at risk of other infections beginning, If someone sneezes of coughs and a tiny droplet goes into your eye, you have the virus and you do not know and so it is spreading and spreading. It is usually found in animals but this, like SARS & MERS mutated, I am guessing why, and transformed, like them, to human to human. This is new, it does not have a name, but is one of the corona type viruses but 'special' in the speed it is spreading and how. You could be infected by someone you never know and infect many you do not know. Those aged 16 - 60 are reasonably safe proving they have no immune suppressant conditions, those younger and older are in a higher risk group due to age. If it gets worse stay home and have contact only with immediate family, deny visitors, wear non-latex medical gloves and medical mask and wrap round safety glasses if you need to go out, some may choose to do this anyway. I have just been to the local store here in the UK for groceries and took a shopping trolley and thought nothing of it, because I did not know it is able to live for up to 5 days on hard surfaces. I am not taking any measures now, but it is advised to avoid public places and big crowds. We none of us know who may be contagious and so be aware anyone could be now. Public bathrooms, buses, trains, planes and such should be avoided if possible. So the masks above will give some protection, but their eyes are not protected. I am not worried but do worry about our vulnerable people and so thought I would share this. Take care.

snippet.textDisplay:
I’m surprised that the officials are basically saying if the virus hasn’t been confirmed to be yet so severe or unless major cases happened, we won’t take much action on a public wide scale in a non direct manner.

This pretty much feels like how the Chinese government handled it in Wuhan - but their statement was “we need to confirm this with the higher ups, before making a public warning on prevention” - during the first day of knowing the virus, and look at China now.

Comparing to that, officials here are doing much better, but is it enough?

For disclaimers, that statement came from various sources, which may not be reliable. But there has been a video on YouTube where a Wuhan citizen is risking his life on criticizing the government’s actions during the very beginning of knowing the virus - he claims that “there were a ton of people not taking precautions (e.g. wearing masks, etc.) even on the 2nd day of knowing the virus due to no strict warnings from the government”.
